- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to learn point processes based on incomplete data using Hawkes processes, which is a type of machine learning model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves data synthesis, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence to generate more training data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Hawkes processes are often used to model event sequences in social and information networks, which is the focus of this paper. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm to learn point processes from incomplete data, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper discusses the rationality and feasibility of the proposed method in terms of arguments based on likelihood, which is a statistical concept.
